# Chapter 3 - Strings

This chapter covers string handling in Java and how to work with text data effectively.

## Topics Covered:
- Introduction to Strings
- String Declaration and Initialization
- String Methods (length, charAt, substring, etc.)
- String Comparison
- String Manipulation

## Practice Programs:
- String input and output
- Reverse a string
- Check palindrome string
- String concatenation
- Character counting

## Purpose:
- Understand how to work with text data
- Learn built-in string methods
- Improve problem-solving using strings

This chapter builds a strong foundation for handling text-based data in Java.
